&lt;blockquote&gt;
&lt;ol&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;armory-inline&quot; data-armory-embed=&quot;skills&quot; data-armory-ids=&quot;5538&quot;&gt;&lt;&#x2F;span&gt; Shatterstone (&lt;span class=&quot;armory-inline&quot; data-armory-embed=&quot;skills&quot; data-armory-ids=&quot;5493&quot;&gt;&lt;&#x2F;span&gt; Water Attunement Scepter 2)&lt;&#x2F;li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;armory-inline&quot; data-armory-embed=&quot;skills&quot; data-armory-ids=&quot;5556&quot;&gt;&lt;&#x2F;span&gt; Freezing Gust (&lt;span class=&quot;armory-inline&quot; data-armory-embed=&quot;skills&quot; data-armory-ids=&quot;5493&quot;&gt;&lt;&#x2F;span&gt; Water Attunement Focus 4)&lt;&#x2F;li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;armory-inline&quot; data-armory-embed=&quot;skills&quot; data-armory-ids=&quot;5490&quot;&gt;&lt;&#x2F;span&gt; Comet (&lt;span class=&quot;armory-inline&quot; data-armory-embed=&quot;skills&quot; data-armory-ids=&quot;5493&quot;&gt;&lt;&#x2F;span&gt; Water Attunement Focus 5)&lt;&#x2F;li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;armory-inline&quot; data-armory-embed=&quot;skills&quot; data-armory-ids=&quot;5562&quot;&gt;&lt;&#x2F;span&gt; Gale (&lt;span class=&quot;armory-inline&quot; data-armory-embed=&quot;skills&quot; data-armory-ids=&quot;5494&quot;&gt;&lt;&#x2F;span&gt; Air Attunement Focus 5)&lt;&#x2F;li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;armory-inline&quot; data-armory-embed=&quot;skills&quot; data-armory-ids=&quot;45742&quot;&gt;&lt;&#x2F;span&gt; Glacial Drift (Dual Scepter 3)&lt;&#x2F;li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;armory-inline&quot; data-armory-embed=&quot;skills&quot; data-armory-ids=&quot;40794&quot;&gt;&lt;&#x2F;span&gt; Earthen Synergy (Dual Scepter 3)&lt;&#x2F;li&gt;
&lt;&#x2F;ol&gt;
&lt;&#x2F;blockquote&gt;
&lt;p&gt;However, these skills are locked behind elements that you do not use in your rotation. To fully utilize your CC, you should use the following CC Loop.&lt;&#x2F;p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;CC Loop&lt;&#x2F;strong&gt;&lt;&#x2F;p&gt;
&lt;blockquote&gt;
&lt;ol&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;armory-inline&quot; data-armory-embed=&quot;skills&quot; data-armory-ids=&quot;5493&quot;&gt;&lt;&#x2F;span&gt; Water Attunement&lt;&#x2F;li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;armory-inline&quot; data-armory-embed=&quot;skills&quot; data-armory-ids=&quot;5538&quot;&gt;&lt;&#x2F;span&gt; Shatterstone (&lt;span class=&quot;armory-inline&quot; data-armory-embed=&quot;skills&quot; data-armory-ids=&quot;5493&quot;&gt;&lt;&#x2F;span&gt; Water Attunement Scepter 2)&lt;&#x2F;li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;armory-inline&quot; data-armory-embed=&quot;skills&quot; data-armory-ids=&quot;5494&quot;&gt;&lt;&#x2F;span&gt; Air Attunement&lt;&#x2F;li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;armory-inline&quot; data-armory-embed=&quot;skills&quot; data-armory-ids=&quot;45742&quot;&gt;&lt;&#x2F;span&gt; Glacial Drift (Dual Scepter 3)&lt;&#x2F;li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;armory-inline&quot; data-armory-embed=&quot;skills&quot; data-armory-ids=&quot;5556&quot;&gt;&lt;&#x2F;span&gt; Freezing Gust (&lt;span class=&quot;armory-inline&quot; data-armory-embed=&quot;skills&quot; data-armory-ids=&quot;5493&quot;&gt;&lt;&#x2F;span&gt; Water Attunement Focus 4)&lt;&#x2F;li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;armory-inline&quot; data-armory-embed=&quot;skills&quot; data-armory-ids=&quot;5490&quot;&gt;&lt;&#x2F;span&gt; Comet (&lt;span class=&quot;armory-inline&quot; data-armory-embed=&quot;skills&quot; data-armory-ids=&quot;5493&quot;&gt;&lt;&#x2F;span&gt; Water Attunement Focus 5)&lt;&#x2F;li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;armory-inline&quot; data-armory-embed=&quot;skills&quot; data-armory-ids=&quot;5495&quot;&gt;&lt;&#x2F;span&gt; Earth Attunement&lt;&#x2F;li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;armory-inline&quot; data-armory-embed=&quot;skills&quot; data-armory-ids=&quot;5562&quot;&gt;&lt;&#x2F;span&gt; Gale (&lt;span class=&quot;armory-inline&quot; data-armory-embed=&quot;skills&quot; data-armory-ids=&quot;5494&quot;&gt;&lt;&#x2F;span&gt; Air Attunement Focus 5)&lt;&#x2F;li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;armory-inline&quot; data-armory-embed=&quot;skills&quot; data-armory-ids=&quot;40794&quot;&gt;&lt;&#x2F;span&gt; Earthen Synergy (Dual Scepter 3)&lt;&#x2F;li&gt;
&lt;&#x2F;ol&gt;
&lt;&#x2F;blockquote&gt;
&lt;p&gt;And continue your rotation from Step #3 in the Main Loop.&lt;&#x2F;p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This may seem very intimidating at first, but in simplified form it is just:&lt;&#x2F;p&gt;
&lt;blockquote&gt;
&lt;ol&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;armory-inline&quot; data-armory-embed=&quot;skills&quot; data-armory-ids=&quot;5493&quot;&gt;&lt;&#x2F;span&gt; Water Attunement 2&lt;&#x2F;li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;armory-inline&quot; data-armory-embed=&quot;skills&quot; data-armory-ids=&quot;5494&quot;&gt;&lt;&#x2F;span&gt; Air Attunement 3 4 5&lt;&#x2F;li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;armory-inline&quot; data-armory-embed=&quot;skills&quot; data-armory-ids=&quot;5495&quot;&gt;&lt;&#x2F;span&gt; Earth Attunement 3 5&lt;&#x2F;li&gt;
&lt;&#x2F;ol&gt;
&lt;&#x2F;blockquote&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Sometimes, you do not need so much CC, in that case you can use a shortened loop.&lt;&#x2F;p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Short CC Loop&lt;&#x2F;strong&gt;&lt;&#x2F;p&gt;
&lt;blockquote&gt;
&lt;ol&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;armory-inline&quot; data-armory-embed=&quot;skills&quot; data-armory-ids=&quot;5493&quot;&gt;&lt;&#x2F;span&gt; Water Attunement&lt;&#x2F;li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;armory-inline&quot; data-armory-embed=&quot;skills&quot; data-armory-ids=&quot;5538&quot;&gt;&lt;&#x2F;span&gt; Shatterstone (&lt;span class=&quot;armory-inline&quot; data-armory-embed=&quot;skills&quot; data-armory-ids=&quot;5493&quot;&gt;&lt;&#x2F;span&gt; Water Attunement Scepter 2)&lt;&#x2F;li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;armory-inline&quot; data-armory-embed=&quot;skills&quot; data-armory-ids=&quot;5495&quot;&gt;&lt;&#x2F;span&gt; Earth Attunement&lt;&#x2F;li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;armory-inline&quot; data-armory-embed=&quot;skills&quot; data-armory-ids=&quot;5556&quot;&gt;&lt;&#x2F;span&gt; Freezing Gust (&lt;span class=&quot;armory-inline&quot; data-armory-embed=&quot;skills&quot; data-armory-ids=&quot;5493&quot;&gt;&lt;&#x2F;span&gt; Water Attunement Focus 4)&lt;&#x2F;li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;armory-inline&quot; data-armory-embed=&quot;skills&quot; data-armory-ids=&quot;5490&quot;&gt;&lt;&#x2F;span&gt; Comet (&lt;span class=&quot;armory-inline&quot; data-armory-embed=&quot;skills&quot; data-armory-ids=&quot;5493&quot;&gt;&lt;&#x2F;span&gt; Water Attunement Focus 5)&lt;&#x2F;li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;armory-inline&quot; data-armory-embed=&quot;skills&quot; data-armory-ids=&quot;46014&quot;&gt;&lt;&#x2F;span&gt; Stone Tide (Dual Septer 3)&lt;&#x2F;li&gt;
&lt;&#x2F;ol&gt;
&lt;&#x2F;blockquote&gt;
&lt;p&gt;And continue your rotation from Step #3 in the Main Loop.&lt;&#x2F;p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Once again, the simplified form will look like:&lt;&#x2F;p&gt;
&lt;blockquote&gt;
&lt;ol&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;armory-inline&quot; data-armory-embed=&quot;skills&quot; data-armory-ids=&quot;5493&quot;&gt;&lt;&#x2F;span&gt; Water Attunement 2&lt;&#x2F;li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;armory-inline&quot; data-armory-embed=&quot;skills&quot; data-armory-ids=&quot;5495&quot;&gt;&lt;&#x2F;span&gt; Earth Attunement 3 4 5&lt;&#x2F;li&gt;
&lt;&#x2F;ol&gt;
&lt;&#x2F;blockquote&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Having to CC will result in a significant DPS loss, and it is recommended to bring this class only if the fight has very low CC pressure, no CC at all, or if your supports are able to carry the CC.&lt;&#x2F;p&gt;
&lt;h2 id=&quot;advanced-tips&quot;&gt;Advanced Tips&lt;&#x2F;h2&gt;
&lt;hr &#x2F;&gt;
&lt;p&gt;To convert this build to do more damage at ranged, replace:&lt;&#x2F;p&gt;
&lt;blockquote&gt;
&lt;ol&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;armory-inline&quot; data-armory-embed=&quot;skills&quot; data-armory-ids=&quot;40183&quot;&gt;&lt;&#x2F;span&gt; Primordial Stance&lt;&#x2F;li&gt;
&lt;&#x2F;ol&gt;
&lt;&#x2F;blockquote&gt;
&lt;p&gt;with either:&lt;&#x2F;p&gt;
&lt;blockquote&gt;
&lt;ol&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;armory-inline&quot; data-armory-embed=&quot;skills&quot; data-armory-ids=&quot;5506&quot;&gt;&lt;&#x2F;span&gt; Glyph of Elemental Power&lt;&#x2F;li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;armory-inline&quot; data-armory-embed=&quot;skills&quot; data-armory-ids=&quot;5736&quot;&gt;&lt;&#x2F;span&gt; Firestorm&lt;&#x2F;li&gt;
&lt;&#x2F;ol&gt;
&lt;&#x2F;blockquote&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Generally you want to pick &lt;span class=&quot;armory-inline&quot; data-armory-embed=&quot;skills&quot; data-armory-ids=&quot;5506&quot;&gt;&lt;&#x2F;span&gt; Glyph of Elemental Power over &lt;span class=&quot;armory-inline&quot; data-armory-embed=&quot;skills&quot; data-armory-ids=&quot;5736&quot;&gt;&lt;&#x2F;span&gt; Firestorm as &lt;span class=&quot;armory-inline&quot; data-armory-embed=&quot;skills&quot; data-armory-ids=&quot;5506&quot;&gt;&lt;&#x2F;span&gt; Glyph of Elemental Power can be precast, and has no cast time, allowing for minimal impact to your rotation. However, &lt;span class=&quot;armory-inline&quot; data-armory-embed=&quot;skills&quot; data-armory-ids=&quot;5736&quot;&gt;&lt;&#x2F;span&gt; Firestorm tends to do more damage on fights that the bosses that have lower armour, as well as on bosses that do not move much.&lt;&#x2F;p&gt;
&lt;div style=‘clear:both;’&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;&#x2F;div&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Try to use:&lt;&#x2F;p&gt;
&lt;blockquote&gt;
&lt;ol&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;armory-inline&quot; data-armory-embed=&quot;skills&quot; data-armory-ids=&quot;5497&quot;&gt;&lt;&#x2F;span&gt; Flamewall (&lt;span class=&quot;armory-inline&quot; data-armory-embed=&quot;skills&quot; data-armory-ids=&quot;5492&quot;&gt;&lt;&#x2F;span&gt; Fire Attunement Focus 4)&lt;&#x2F;li&gt;
&lt;&#x2F;ol&gt;
&lt;&#x2F;blockquote&gt;
&lt;p&gt;before:&lt;&#x2F;p&gt;
&lt;blockquote&gt;
&lt;ol&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;armory-inline&quot; data-armory-embed=&quot;skills&quot; data-armory-ids=&quot;5692&quot;&gt;&lt;&#x2F;span&gt; Dragon&#x27;s Tooth (&lt;span class=&quot;armory-inline&quot; data-armory-embed=&quot;skills&quot; data-armory-ids=&quot;5492&quot;&gt;&lt;&#x2F;span&gt; Fire Attunement Scepter 2)&lt;&#x2F;li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;armory-inline&quot; data-armory-embed=&quot;skills&quot; data-armory-ids=&quot;5675&quot;&gt;&lt;&#x2F;span&gt; Phoenix (&lt;span class=&quot;armory-inline&quot; data-armory-embed=&quot;skills&quot; data-armory-ids=&quot;5492&quot;&gt;&lt;&#x2F;span&gt; Fire Attunement Scepter 3)&lt;&#x2F;li&gt;
&lt;&#x2F;ol&gt;
&lt;&#x2F;blockquote&gt;
&lt;p&gt;whenever possible as that will allow you to blast might for your squad.&lt;&#x2F;p&gt;
&lt;h2 id=&quot;video&quot;&gt;Video&lt;&#x2F;h2&gt;
&lt;hr &#x2F;&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This bench is done with &lt;span class=&quot;armory-inline&quot; data-armory-embed=&quot;skills&quot; data-armory-ids=&quot;25486&quot;&gt;&lt;&#x2F;span&gt; Glyph of Lesser Elementals despite the inherent RNG of the skill. However, it has not been precast, and will therefore always result in a lower number than using &lt;span class=&quot;armory-inline&quot; data-armory-embed=&quot;skills&quot; data-armory-ids=&quot;5506&quot;&gt;&lt;&#x2F;span&gt; Glyph of Elemental Power. This means that I am able to show off the full rotation and build without inflating the final damage number. I choose to leave it in because I have seen many players who don&#x27;t read and just use &lt;span class=&quot;armory-inline&quot; data-armory-embed=&quot;skills&quot; data-armory-ids=&quot;5506&quot;&gt;&lt;&#x2F;span&gt; Glyph of Elemental Power during the actual fights.&lt;&#x2F;p&gt;
